cause.description:
Esperanza is a nonprofit community development organization focused on serving the most impoverished families in the Dominican Republic and Haiti. Esperanza was founded in 1995 by former Major League Baseball player, Dave Valle and his wife Victoria.

Programs:
1) Microfinance - Our core program enables families to start or expand their own businesses through small loans, insurance, savings and business training to generate income and economic security. 

2) Health Care - In partnership with local medical clinics, Esperanza families receive free preventative health care exams, dental cleanings and basic vaccinations for their children. We also offer special services such as physical therapy, pediatric care,  OBGYN, dentistry and general medicine.

3) Education - We provide business and vocational training for the working poor to start or develop their own business. We also give their families access to computer training courses and our literacy program to increase knowledge and expand their opportunities for the future.

4) Social Mobilization - Through a network of local schools, churches, computer labs and community meetings, Esperanza helps to coordinate community resources and services – leading to a future free from poverty and dependence. 

Please visit our website at www.esperanza.org for more information.

